So user ratings are
something that's

00:17:20.680 --> 00:17:22.940
really important on Google Play.

00:17:22.940 --> 00:17:24.599
Users frequently
use ratings when

00:17:24.599 --> 00:17:26.500
they're comparing
multiple apps and trying

00:17:26.500 --> 00:17:28.530
to decide which one to install.

00:17:28.530 --> 00:17:30.750
And so one thing our most
successful developers

00:17:30.750 --> 00:17:33.870
tell us is that they
want to understand how

00:17:33.870 --> 00:17:35.670
they can improve their reviews.

00:17:35.670 --> 00:17:38.370
And they put a lot of time
into reading those reviews,

00:17:38.370 --> 00:17:40.930
understanding the
complaints that users have,

00:17:40.930 --> 00:17:43.380
reading user requests
for new features,

00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.830
and then a special feature
that we have on Google Play

00:17:45.830 --> 00:17:48.720
is that you can actually post
replies to your user reviews.

00:17:48.720 --> 00:17:51.720
So if a user says,
hey, I have this bug,

00:17:51.720 --> 00:17:55.280
the app crashes for me, maybe
it would be nice if you say,

00:17:55.280 --> 00:17:56.780
thanks, we'll look
into the problem.

00:17:56.780 --> 00:17:59.405
And then after you've fixed it,
you can reply again to the user

00:17:59.405 --> 00:18:01.810
and say, hey, we've
actually fixed that bug.

00:18:01.810 --> 00:18:05.200
Please check it and let us
know if it's working for you.

00:18:05.200 --> 00:18:07.690
And developers have seen
great response from users.

00:18:07.690 --> 00:18:10.530
Users are usually very happy
to have this excellent customer

00:18:10.530 --> 00:18:11.390
service.

00:18:11.390 --> 00:18:14.350
And because your replies
are posted publicly,

00:18:14.350 --> 00:18:16.835
if you respond to a review,
other users going to the store

00:18:16.835 --> 00:18:18.210
and looking at
your app will say,

00:18:18.210 --> 00:18:19.835
wow, this company
is very responsive.

00:18:23.160 --> 00:18:25.840
OK, so one of the
most powerful tools

00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:29.080
that we have in Google Play
is this idea of beta testing

00:18:29.080 --> 00:18:30.800
and staged rollouts.

00:18:30.800 --> 00:18:34.600
So we've seen over 80,000
apps use beta testing

00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:36.622
and staged rollouts
to increase quality.

00:18:36.622 --> 00:18:38.330
And we're seeing more
and more every day.

00:18:38.330 --> 00:18:41.890
In fact, the majority of
our top apps on the store

00:18:41.890 --> 00:18:45.310
use beta testing and staged
rollouts to increase quality.

00:18:45.310 --> 00:18:47.390
And we see that
the average rating

00:18:47.390 --> 00:18:49.500
for apps who have
done beta testing

00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:52.910
is much higher than the average.

00:18:52.910 --> 00:18:56.010
So let's talk about what each of
these different concepts mean.

00:18:56.010 --> 00:18:57.920
So the whole idea
behind beta testing

00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:00.910
is that you can do a
private test of your app.

00:19:00.910 --> 00:19:03.860
So the idea is here, you
can create a Google group

00:19:03.860 --> 00:19:08.810
or a Google+ community, and
users can opt in to view

00:19:08.810 --> 00:19:10.500
the beta software.

00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:12.090
You also get two
different versions

00:19:12.090 --> 00:19:13.560
that you can test
simultaneously.

00:19:13.560 --> 00:19:16.450
We call one alpha, and
one of them is beta.

00:19:16.450 --> 00:19:22.950
And to prevent any leaking of
features or people sharing bugs

00:19:22.950 --> 00:19:26.350
or things like that, we actually
make it so that those users

00:19:26.350 --> 00:19:29.000
in the alpha and the beta
cannot actually leave reviews.

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:31.680
So this means if you're
testing some early software

00:19:31.680 --> 00:19:33.730
with a small group
of beta testers,

00:19:33.730 --> 00:19:37.930
this won't have any negative
impact on your reviews.

00:19:37.930 --> 00:19:41.590
And later, you're actually
able to compare the statistics.

00:19:41.590 --> 00:19:45.750
So for example, you can see how
different metrics like crashes

00:19:45.750 --> 00:19:50.130
vary between your alpha
and beta versions.

00:19:50.130 --> 00:19:52.540
Now, once you've tested
it with a small group

00:19:52.540 --> 00:19:55.490
and you're ready to roll
out to a larger population,

00:19:55.490 --> 00:19:57.050
you can use staged rollouts.

00:19:57.050 --> 00:20:00.050
So the idea here is that
when you release an update

00:20:00.050 --> 00:20:01.790
to your app, you
should be pretty sure

00:20:01.790 --> 00:20:03.039
that it's going to work great.

00:20:03.039 --> 00:20:04.720
But occasionally, we
all have that worry

00:20:04.720 --> 00:20:06.500
that what if there's a bug?

00:20:06.500 --> 00:20:09.110
So staged rollouts lets
you put the new version out

00:20:09.110 --> 00:20:10.950
to a small group of users.

00:20:10.950 --> 00:20:13.840
And so if you do find that
there is an issue early on,

00:20:13.840 --> 00:20:16.750
like let's say users start
leaving bad reviews saying

00:20:16.750 --> 00:20:18.250
that they don't
like the new version

00:20:18.250 --> 00:20:20.220
or you notice a high
rate of crashing,

00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:23.110
you can just stop the rollout
right there, fix the bug,

00:20:23.110 --> 00:20:24.250
and then move on.

00:20:24.250 --> 00:20:28.380
So it keeps bugs from
impacting your whole user base.

00:20:28.380 --> 00:20:30.550
One common thing that
developers ask me a lot

00:20:30.550 --> 00:20:33.600
is, tell me what I
should do on my app next.

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:36.420
And so to try to make this
advice as scalable as possible,

00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:40.580
we have a new area that we call
optimization tips and alerts.

00:20:40.580 --> 00:20:44.850
So what you decide to work on
next can be influenced by this.

00:20:44.850 --> 00:20:47.700
So if we notice any
opportunities for your app

00:20:47.700 --> 00:20:50.390
to improve, we'll give
you an optimization tip.

00:20:50.390 --> 00:20:53.140
So an example of
this might be maybe

00:20:53.140 --> 00:20:56.470
you have an app with a lot of
installs in, let's say, Russia,

00:20:56.470 --> 00:20:58.910
but your app is not
translated into Russian.

00:20:58.910 --> 00:21:00.150
We'll actually let you know.

00:21:00.150 --> 00:21:02.130
And then it's easy to
purchase a translation

00:21:02.130 --> 00:21:03.130
into that new language.

00:21:03.130 --> 00:21:05.710
And this can be a great way
to make sure that you haven't

00:21:05.710 --> 00:21:07.410
missed any opportunities.

00:21:07.410 --> 00:21:10.280
Similarly, if we notice a
problem with your application,

00:21:10.280 --> 00:21:11.690
we'll also let you know.

00:21:11.690 --> 00:21:14.090
So let's say that you publish
a new version of your app,

00:21:14.090 --> 00:21:16.200
and we notice that your
user reviews are much

00:21:16.200 --> 00:21:19.247
lower than your older versions.

00:21:19.247 --> 00:21:21.080
So we'll actually give
you an alert and say,

00:21:21.080 --> 00:21:21.996
you should check this.

00:21:21.996 --> 00:21:23.430
Maybe there's a problem.

00:21:23.430 --> 00:21:26.640
You can also sign up to receive
emails so that you find out

00:21:26.640 --> 00:21:29.880
about these alerts faster.

00:21:29.880 --> 00:21:34.620
So once you understand how
your app is doing overall,

00:21:34.620 --> 00:21:36.030
you want to
understand what users

00:21:36.030 --> 00:21:37.690
are doing inside your app.

00:21:37.690 --> 00:21:40.740
And the easiest way to do
that is Google Analytics.

00:21:40.740 --> 00:21:42.520
Google Analytics is
also very helpful,

00:21:42.520 --> 00:21:44.460
because it works cross platform.

00:21:44.460 --> 00:21:48.090
You may have an Android
app, but maybe also

00:21:48.090 --> 00:21:50.840
apps on other platforms,
and maybe a website as well.

00:21:50.840 --> 00:21:53.130
And Google Analytics
lets you measure users

00:21:53.130 --> 00:21:56.090
across all of these platforms.

00:21:56.090 --> 00:21:58.340
So with just three
easy lines of code,

00:21:58.340 --> 00:22:00.570
you can add Google
Analytics to your app.

00:22:00.570 --> 00:22:04.480
And from there, you can get a
lot of detailed information.

00:22:04.480 --> 00:22:06.070
So one example of
what you can do

00:22:06.070 --> 00:22:07.850
once you've integrated
Google Analytics

00:22:07.850 --> 00:22:10.080
is Google Tag Manager.

00:22:10.080 --> 00:22:13.120
So once you understand what
users do inside your app,

00:22:13.120 --> 00:22:15.330
you probably want to
make little tweaks to it.

00:22:15.330 --> 00:22:17.290
And so Google Tag
Manager actually

00:22:17.290 --> 00:22:19.120
lets you run experiments.

00:22:19.120 --> 00:22:21.740
So for example, I could
have two versions of my app.

00:22:21.740 --> 00:22:25.730
Maybe in one case, the
character in the game is a dog

00:22:25.730 --> 00:22:28.610
and in another case, maybe the
character in the game is a cat.

00:22:28.610 --> 00:22:30.810
And I could do a test
to see whether users

00:22:30.810 --> 00:22:32.680
like cats or dogs better.

00:22:32.680 --> 00:22:35.360
And then if I say I want to
maximize a certain metric,

00:22:35.360 --> 00:22:38.700
like let's say revenue or
time spent in the game,

00:22:38.700 --> 00:22:41.090
then the metric I
choose will be used

00:22:41.090 --> 00:22:43.350
to determine whether the
cat or the dog character

00:22:43.350 --> 00:22:44.260
is the winner.

00:22:44.260 --> 00:22:46.450
And over time, it will
switch more and more people

00:22:46.450 --> 00:22:50.970
over to the version that gives
the result that I prefer.

00:22:50.970 --> 00:22:52.840
A common question
that users ask a lot

00:22:52.840 --> 00:22:56.562
is, I would like to know how
people find my application.

00:22:56.562 --> 00:22:58.020
And one of the best
ways to do this

00:22:58.020 --> 00:23:00.219
is the Google Play
Referral Flow Report.

00:23:00.219 --> 00:23:01.760
And this is a unique
feature that you

00:23:01.760 --> 00:23:04.690
can get if you're using
Google Analytics in your app.

00:23:04.690 --> 00:23:07.970
This allows you to track the
effectiveness of each campaign

00:23:07.970 --> 00:23:09.700
that you run on Google Play.

00:23:09.700 --> 00:23:12.150
So for every single
campaign that you have,

00:23:12.150 --> 00:23:15.740
you can see how many users view
your app in the Play Store,

00:23:15.740 --> 00:23:18.720
how many install your app,
and how many launch your app.

00:23:18.720 --> 00:23:21.350
And this allows you to
track that conversion funnel

00:23:21.350 --> 00:23:24.280
and understand which campaigns
perform best so that you can

00:23:24.280 --> 00:23:26.570
optimize your marketing
budget and invest more

00:23:26.570 --> 00:23:29.960
in the campaigns that work well.

00:23:29.960 --> 00:23:33.280
OK, so another
sophisticated thing

00:23:33.280 --> 00:23:34.890
that Google Analytics
can do for you

00:23:34.890 --> 00:23:37.350
is allow you to define
the segments of your users

00:23:37.350 --> 00:23:40.420
that are most valuable, and
then track them over time

00:23:40.420 --> 00:23:42.580
and compare them to
the average user.

00:23:42.580 --> 00:23:44.260
So for example, I
can say that I'm

00:23:44.260 --> 00:23:48.310
very interested in users who
have gotten to level seven

00:23:48.310 --> 00:23:51.720
in my game, have
spent more than $5,

00:23:51.720 --> 00:23:54.750
and installed my
application in December.

00:23:54.750 --> 00:23:57.410
And I can track that
group of users over time

00:23:57.410 --> 00:24:00.380
and see how they respond to
different changes in the app

00:24:00.380 --> 00:24:04.530
or to see how many of them
stay engaged in the long term.

00:24:04.530 --> 00:24:06.580
We've seen a lot of
developers on Google Play

00:24:06.580 --> 00:24:09.880
be able to grow their revenue
into significant businesses,

00:24:09.880 --> 00:24:12.220
and so we've given much
more advanced reporting

00:24:12.220 --> 00:24:13.677
around revenue.

00:24:13.677 --> 00:24:15.510
So in addition to showing
you total revenue,

00:24:15.510 --> 00:24:17.750
we also show the average
revenue per paying

00:24:17.750 --> 00:24:21.320
user, the number of
buyers, and also allow

00:24:21.320 --> 00:24:25.245
you to see breakdowns by country
of how much different revenue

00:24:25.245 --> 00:24:26.470
you're making in each market.

00:24:26.470 --> 00:24:28.136
And this can be really
helpful as you're

00:24:28.136 --> 00:24:30.130
distributing your apps
and games globally

00:24:30.130 --> 00:24:32.400
and you want to understand
the financial performance

00:24:32.400 --> 00:24:35.080
of each market.

00:24:35.080 --> 00:24:37.380
One common request that
we had from developers,

00:24:37.380 --> 00:24:40.050
especially those who have
a large number of apps

00:24:40.050 --> 00:24:43.840
or a large number of languages,
is that updating your apps

00:24:43.840 --> 00:24:45.990
was getting pretty
time consuming.

00:24:45.990 --> 00:24:48.380
So if you're spending a
lot of time doing updates,

00:24:48.380 --> 00:24:51.410
especially if you have a lot of
apps or a lot of translations

00:24:51.410 --> 00:24:54.520
into different languages,
the developer publishing API

00:24:54.520 --> 00:24:56.300
may be helpful for you.

00:24:56.300 --> 00:24:59.200
So it's able to
upload your APKs,

00:24:59.200 --> 00:25:01.640
you can manage alpha
and beta testing,

00:25:01.640 --> 00:25:04.720
you can upload your
localized graphics and text,

00:25:04.720 --> 00:25:06.714
and it can be very
helpful to make sure

00:25:06.714 --> 00:25:09.130
that you don't make any mistakes
in the publishing process

00:25:09.130 --> 00:25:12.730
and that you can spend more time
building great apps and games

00:25:12.730 --> 00:25:15.240
rather than uploading them.

